Package: imagealgorithm
Type: Package
Title: An algorithm used on images to convert the colors of each pixel to grey, red, green or blue
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Christina Tsagkogianni <christina.tsagkogianni.2@ki.se>
Maintainer: Christina Tsagkogianni <christina.tsagkogianni.2@ki.se>
Description: A function that takes an image as input and returns the same image with the colors of each pixel converted to grey, red, green or blue, depending on the filter selected. The package also contains 5 filters (bw, blue, green, red, grey) that can be used to change the colour of the input image.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports: magick, grDevices
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
